Vellum, about 12 in. by 8 7/8, consisting of 33 leaves (Add. 12,142, foll. 74—107), the last of which is much soiled and torn. The quires are numbered with both letters and arithmetical figures (e. g., foll. 81, ܝܓ
; 93, ܝܗ
); the later numeration with letters is in part erroneous. Twelve quires and some leaves are wanting at the beginning, and at least several leaves at the end. Each page is divided into two columns, of from 23 to 27 lines.
